Fresh off a world tour where he performed at sold out concerts at major venues like Indigo 02 Arena in London, Howard Event Center in Washington, Amazura concert hall in New York City and more, Nigerian pop star, Runtown is back in the country for more shows.This time, the Eric Many front line act continues his winning streak as he's been unveiled as one of the headliners for the 2017 GLO Mega Music Nationwide Tour.The tour will see Runtown perform in 27 Cities across Nigeria starting from April 7, 2017. He'll be joined by other superstars like Olamide, Psquare, Flavour and more.Meanwhile, he's also putting finishing touches to his rehearsals ahead of his April 14th concert at Landmark Event center, Lagos tagged 'One Night Only'.